Relevant specification topics include: phospholipids, DNA/RNA structure, DNA replication, ATP, inorganic ions, cell membranes, digestion/absorption, protein synthesis, meiosis, photosynthesis (RuBP, GP, TP, NADP), respiration, nutrient cycles, nerve impulses, synaptic transmission, skeletal muscles, cyclic AMP, water potential, recombinant DNA technology.

Must cover at least four different topic areas for highest marks. Must demonstrate importance/function, not just name phosphorus-containing substances.

