Relevant specification topics include: phospholipids, proteins, ATP, water, cell structure, cell division, membrane transport, immune system, SA:V ratio, gas exchange, digestion/absorption, mass transport in animals and plants, protein synthesis, photosynthesis, respiration, IAA/plant hormones, receptors, cardiac cycle, nerve impulses, synapses, muscles, homeostasis, blood glucose, water potential, gene expression.

Must cover at least four different topic areas for highest marks. Must discuss mechanisms and importance.

